---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="GeoScore - Free GEO Audit Tool" schema={{
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: [
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What is GEO?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'GEO (Generative Engine Optimization) is the practice of optimizing your website to be discovered, understood, and cited by AI-powered search engines such as ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews, Claude, and Gemini. It focuses on AI crawler access, machine-readable content (llms.txt, JSON-LD schema), and authority signals (E-E-A-T).'
      }
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How is GEO different from SEO?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'SEO optimizes for ranked lists of blue links on search engines like Google and Bing. GEO optimizes for being cited as a source in AI-generated answers. They overlap heavily &mdash; good content, structured data, and authority help both &mdash; but GEO requires explicit AI-crawler allowance in robots.txt, an llms.txt file, and machine-parseable schema for AI models.'
      }
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What is llms.txt?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'llms.txt is a markdown file placed at the root of your website (yoursite.com/llms.txt) that provides AI models with a curated summary of your site: what it is, who it serves, and which pages matter most. It is the machine-readable equivalent of an About page, designed to be ingested by ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, and other LLM-powered crawlers in a single fetch.'
      }
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How does GeoScore work?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'GeoScore audits any public URL across 12 dimensions of GEO readiness (AI crawlability, llms.txt presence, structured data, meta tags, content quality, E-E-A-T signals, brand entity, citation readiness, discovery, agent-friendliness, and freshness), producing a 0-100 score plus a prioritized list of fixes. The audit runs entirely in your browser; your URLs are not stored.'
      }
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Is GeoScore free?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'Yes. GeoScore is 100% free and open-source under the MIT License. There is no signup, no paywall, and no per-audit limit. The source code is available on GitHub at github.com/qq136692547-cmyk/geo-score.'
      }
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Which AI crawlers should I allow in robots.txt?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'At minimum, allow: GPTBot and OAI-SearchBot (OpenAI/ChatGPT), ClaudeBot and anthropic-ai (Anthropic/Claude), PerplexityBot (Perplexity), Google-Extended (Google Gemini and AI Overviews), and CCBot (Common Crawl, used by many models). GeoScore will tell you exactly which crawlers you are currently blocking.'
      }
    }
  ]
}}>
  <!-- Bootstrap: stub global functions until boot.js module loads -->
  <script is:inline>
    (function() {
      var queue = [];
      ["startAudit","showBatchInput","showComparison","startBatchAudit","runComparison","doExport"].forEach(function(n) {
        window[n] = function() { queue.push({ n: n, a: arguments }); };
      });
      window.__geoFlush = function() { queue.splice(0).forEach(function(q) { window[q.n].apply(null, q.a); }); };
    })();
  </script>
  
  
  <section class="hero-grid-bg text-center py-8 md:py-16" id="hero-section">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-brand-500/10 text-brand-400 border border-brand-500/20 mb-6">
        <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-geo-500 loading-dot" style="display:inline-block"></span>
        Generative Engine Optimization
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold mb-6 tracking-tight leading-[1.1]">
        Check Your Website&rsquo;s<br/>
        <span class="gradient-text">GEO Readiness</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-2">
        Score your site&rsquo;s AI search visibility &mdash; ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, Gemini, Google AI Overviews.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-10">
        12 dimensions &middot; 100-point scoring &middot; Free &amp; open-source
      </p>

      <div class="max-w-xl mx-auto mb-6 px-1">
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
          <div class="flex-1 relative">
            <svg class="absolute left-4 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-5 h-5 text-gray-500" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 8v4l3 3"/></svg>
            <input id="url-input" type="text" placeholder="输入网址，如 geoscore.help" class="w-full pl-12 pr-5 py-3.5 rounded-xl bg-white/5 text-white placeholder-gray-500 border border-gray-600 focus:border-brand-500 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-500/30 text-lg transition" onkeydown="if(event.key==='Enter'){document.getElementById('audit-btn').click();}" />
          </div>
          <button id="audit-btn" class="px-8 py-3.5 rounded-xl font-semibold text-white bg-gradient-to-r from-geo-600 to-brand-600 hover:from-geo-500 hover:to-brand-500 active:from-geo-700 active:to-brand-700 transition shadow-lg shadow-brand-500/20 hover:shadow-brand-500/30 whitespace-nowrap w-full sm:w-auto">Start Audit</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 text-xs">
        <a id="batch-link" class="text-gray-500 hover:text-brand-400 transition cursor-pointer underline underline-offset-2">Batch audit via sitemap</a>
        <span class="text-gray-600">|</span>
        <a id="compare-link" class="text-gray-500 hover:text-brand-400 transition cursor-pointer underline underline-offset-2" style="display:none">Compare sites</a>
      </div>
      <div id="batch-section" class="hidden max-w-lg mx-auto mt-4 card p-4">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2 text-gray-300">Batch Audit from Sitemap</h3>
        <input id="sitemap-url" type="url" placeholder="e.g. example.com/sitemap.xml" class="w-full px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-white/5 text-white placeholder-gray-500 border border-gray-600 focus:border-brand-500 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand-500/30 text-sm transition mb-3" />
        <button id="batch-btn" class="px-5 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-semibold text-white bg-gradient-to-r from-geo-600 to-brand-600 hover:from-geo-500 hover:to-brand-500 transition">Start Batch Scan</button>
        <div id="batch-progress" class="mt-3 hidden">
          <div class="w-full h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-700/50 overflow-hidden"><div id="batch-bar" class="h-full rounded-full bg-brand-500" style="width:0%"></div></div>
          <p id="batch-status" class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1"></p>
        </div>
        <div id="batch-results" class="mt-3 text-xs text-left max-h-60 overflow-y-auto"></div>
      </div>
      <div id="compare-section" class="hidden max-w-lg mx-auto mt-4 card p-4" style="display:none">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2 text-gray-300">Select sites to compare</h3>
        <div id="compare-list" class="space-y-1 mb-3 max-h-40 overflow-y-auto"></div>
        <button id="compare-btn" class="px-4 py-1.5 rounded-lg text-xs font-semibold text-white bg-brand-600 hover:bg-brand-500 transition">Compare Selected</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div id="loading-section" class="hidden max-w-lg mx-auto py-12">
    <div class="card p-8 text-center">
      <div class="scan-bar rounded-full mb-8"></div>
      <div class="space-y-1 mb-8" id="scan-steps">
        <div class="scan-step active" data-step="0"><span class="scan-step-dot"></span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Connecting to server</span></div>
        <div class="scan-step" data-step="1"><span class="scan-step-dot"></span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Fetching robots.txt &amp; AI directives</span></div>
        <div class="scan-step" data-step="2"><span class="scan-step-dot"></span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Analyzing llms.txt &amp; AI guidance</span></div>
        <div class="scan-step" data-step="3"><span class="scan-step-dot"></span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Parsing structured data &amp; schema</span></div>
        <div class="scan-step" data-step="4"><span class="scan-step-dot"></span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Checking meta tags &amp; social signals</span></div>
        <div class="scan-step" data-step="5"><span class="scan-step-dot"></span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Evaluating content &amp; E-E-A-T signals</span></div>
        <div class="scan-step" data-step="6"><span class="scan-step-dot"></span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Calculating final score</span></div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Analyzing <span class="text-gray-300 font-mono" id="scanning-url"></span></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="report-section" class="hidden max-w-6xl mx-auto"></div>
  <div id="history-root" class="max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8"></div>

  <!-- SEO Content Section -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-12 border-t border-gray-700/50">

    <!-- Educational intro: What is GEO? (300+ words for AI crawlers) -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center mb-6">What is GEO (Generative Engine Optimization)?</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        <p class="mb-4">
          <strong class="text-white">Generative Engine Optimization (GEO)</strong> is the practice of optimizing your website so that AI-powered search engines &mdash; including ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews, Claude, and Gemini &mdash; can discover, understand, and cite your content. Unlike traditional SEO, which optimizes for ranked lists of blue links, GEO optimizes for being selected as a cited source in AI-generated answers.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          The shift is fundamental. In 2026, more than 40% of search sessions on Google now end without a click, and a growing share of queries never reach Google at all &mdash; users go directly to ChatGPT or Perplexity. For content creators, SaaS founders, and publishers, this means a new discipline is required. Your site needs to be readable to AI crawlers (robots.txt, llms.txt), machine-parseable (JSON-LD schema), and authoritative (E-E-A-T signals, third-party citations).
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          GeoScore measures 12 dimensions of this readiness: AI crawlability (which crawlers can access your site), AI guidance (whether you provide a curated llms.txt), structured data (JSON-LD coverage and quality), meta and social signals, content quality and depth, E-E-A-T signals (author bylines, trust pages, reviews), brand and entity presence, citation readiness (external sources, expert quotes, .edu/.gov links), discovery (sitemap, AI-specific endpoints like /ai/summary.json), agent-friendliness (API documentation, structured outputs), and content freshness.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Each audit produces a 0&ndash;100 score, a radar chart of the 12 dimensions, and a prioritized list of fixes. The tool also auto-generates three fix files you can deploy immediately: a production-ready llms.txt, an AI-crawler-friendly robots.txt, and a JSON-LD snippet for Organization, Article, FAQ, and HowTo schema. The audit runs entirely client-side and your URLs are not stored.
        </p>
        <p>
          If your site scores below 60, the most common cause is robots.txt blocking AI crawlers by default. Adding GPTBot, ClaudeBot, PerplexityBot, and Google-Extended to the allow list, and shipping an llms.txt, typically raises the score by 20&ndash;30 points in a single deployment. The highest-scoring sites combine technical compliance with content depth, source citations, and structured data that AI models can parse in one pass.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center mb-8">Free GEO Tools</h2>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center mb-8">Free GEO Tools</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-12">
      <a href="/tools/llms-txt-checker" class="card card-hover card-lift p-6 block">
        <div class="text-geo-400 text-sm font-mono mb-2">/tools/llms-txt-checker</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">llms.txt Checker</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Check if your site has the AI guidance file that helps ChatGPT, Claude, and Perplexity understand your content.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/tools/robots-txt-ai-checker" class="card card-hover card-lift p-6 block">
        <div class="text-brand-400 text-sm font-mono mb-2">/tools/robots-txt-ai-checker</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Robots.txt AI Checker</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Verify your robots.txt isn't blocking GPTBot, ClaudeBot, PerplexityBot, and other AI crawlers.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/tools/ai-readiness-score" class="card card-hover card-lift p-6 block">
        <div class="text-brand-400 text-sm font-mono mb-2">/tools/ai-readiness-score</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">AI Readiness Score</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Get a 0-100 score across 12 dimensions of AI search visibility with actionable fixes.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center mb-8">Learn GEO</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-12">
      <a href="/blog/what-is-geo" class="card card-hover card-lift p-6 block">
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">Guide · 8 min</div>
        <h3 class="text-base font-bold mb-2">What is GEO?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Complete introduction to Generative Engine Optimization and the 12 dimensions of readiness.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/geo-vs-seo" class="card card-hover card-lift p-6 block">
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">Guide · 10 min</div>
        <h3 class="text-base font-bold mb-2">GEO vs SEO</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">What's the difference? Target engines, crawlers, content strategy, and how they work together.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/how-to-write-llms-txt" class="card card-hover card-lift p-6 block">
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">Tutorial · 12 min</div>
        <h3 class="text-base font-bold mb-2">How to Write llms.txt</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Step-by-step guide with real examples for creating an llms.txt file for your website.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/ai-search-engine-list" class="card card-hover card-lift p-6 block">
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">Reference · 9 min</div>
        <h3 class="text-base font-bold mb-2">AI Search Engine List</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Complete list of AI crawlers — GPTBot, ClaudeBot, PerplexityBot — and how to allow them.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12">
      <a href="/about" class="card card-hover card-lift p-6 block">
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">Reference</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Scoring Methodology</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Detailed breakdown of how GeoScore calculates your 0-100 score across 12 dimensions.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="https://github.com/qq136692547-cmyk/geo-optimization-handbook" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="card card-hover card-lift p-6 block">
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">External Resource</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">GEO Optimization Handbook</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Comprehensive handbook covering advanced GEO strategies and best practices.</p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Why GeoScore?</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-left">
          <div class="text-geo-500 text-3xl font-extrabold mb-2">12</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Dimensions analyzed — from AI crawlability to citation readiness</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-left">
          <div class="text-brand-500 text-3xl font-extrabold mb-2">60+</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Individual checks across all dimensions, with specific fix recommendations</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-left">
          <div class="text-geo-500 text-3xl font-extrabold mb-2">100%</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Free and open-source — no signup, no paywall, no limits</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<script src="../scripts/boot.js"></script>
